  "prompt": "Why mobile phone is also know as cell phone?",
  "response": "The term \"cell phone\" comes from the cellular network technology that these phones use to connect to the network. Here's why:\n\n*   **Cellular Network:** Mobile phone networks are divided into geographic areas called \"cells.\" Each cell has a base station (a cell tower) that handles communication within that specific area.\n*   **Cellular Technology:** As a mobile phone user moves from one cell to another, the network automatically hands off the connection from one cell tower to the next, ensuring seamless communication without interruption. This technology is called cellular technology.\n\nBecause these phones rely on this cellular network structure, they became commonly known as \"cell phones.\" \"Mobile phone\" is a more general term that simply refers to a phone that can be used while moving around, but \"cell phone\" specifically highlights the underlying technology that makes this mobility possible.",
